GO4CSS Mod beta v1.2

GO4CSS is exact port of CS:GO maps to CS:S.

Includes:

- CS:GO de_dust2_beta3 map
- CS:GO de_dust_beta3 map
- CS:GO de_inferno_csgo map
- CS:GO de_lake_go4css_beta1 map
- CS:GO de_nuke_go4css_beta2 map
- CS:GO de_train_csgo map
- CS:GO Blood Decals
- CS:GO Weapons Sounds
- CS:GO Footsteps Sounds
- CS:GO Bullet Impact Sounds

Features:

- Radar/HDR/Color Correction/Bots Navigation/Optimizations for higher FPS
- Everything is packed in bsp files, so mod will not overwrite game textures or sounds.

Authors of GO4CSS:

b00bs & Saidteshnologi

Changelog from v1.1 to v1.2:

- fixed disappearing models after alt-tab
- fixed conflicts with original dust2-dust maps
- fixed loudness of footsteps sounds
- dust radar corrected
- added helicopter to dust map
- and other small corrections.

My first Counter Strike Source map, based in a conspiracy theory. Nothing religiou. I hope you enjoy xD.

I wasnt going to remake iceworld but i saw .Krusty's neon texture tutorial and began to play around with the settings in source SDK untill it looked very nice to me, so i decided to make some different versions and upload them.
And thats what came out.

Don't ask me why all three maps are named fy_iceworld_orig, thats just because most people know what the map will look like then, thats why i kept it.

As allways im using different textures and skyboxes to make it look nicer.
Also hdr is enabled in these maps to make the neontextures glow effect more visible, although thers still the problem with the weapons glowing to much because of the reflections, i hope i will get to know how to fix that in the future.
If you wanna get rid of it just dont enable hdr, BUT not enableing or disableing hdr will also stop the glow effect of neon textures and stuff..


Credits:

.Krusty - neon stripes tutorial
komaokc - texturepack and skybox
Cow-Grain - grass texture
Gatorlangman - egypt textures
ShoX! - neon textures

For those who know how to stop the weapons from glowing to much without disableing hdr, please tell me i really wanna fix this.

The ct's are in town and the terrorist's

hit 6am and the sun's coming up but it looks like
a storms brewing! So will the ct get they breakfast??
Only you can save your banana's and melon's!!! Go Go Go!!!

----------------------------------------------------------->

These are the 3rd and final version'S of my map.

1.Fixed market sound looping and stuttering.

2.Added a few new sounds

3.Added crazy weather such as: Realistic thunder
and lighterning aswell as ground rumble's and rain.
All the weather has it's own sounds which include's
wind, thunder, rain and realistic rumble's.

4.Added a few more props.

5.Map is now at the break of dawn.

6.Added realistic bomb site with a extra massive boom!

7.Added a secret weapon and a extra 2 smoke nade's.

8.Nav file's are now debugged and bots work great,
nav is saved into the bsp file's using Pakrat.

9.Fixed skybox being to close to some brush face's
which was making some building's appear invisible.

10.Made a m4a1 version for those people who like that gun
more than the ak47 but they is still 4 ak47's on the map :)

Hope you enjoy my final version's, look out for my cbble reflect

* * * * * * * * * * * * * DEAGLE CUP MAPS * * * * * * * * * * * * * By Rokusho Rokusho39@Hotmail.com www.sourcejunky.com This trio of maps was developed for the Source Junky Deagle Tourney Everything is BSPZipped as always, no need to DL anything extra. DeagleCup_Map1 Max Players: 12 Build Time: 4 hours Compile Time: 2 minutes, 35 seconds Average FPS: 195 de_dust2 Average FPS: 92 A very simple map, with plenty of cover and options. Big enough to have plenty of fun with 12 players, small enough for 2 to get into tense battles. Mainly designed to have an industrial feel to it, prop limit low to maintain good FPS. Very exciting map to play. DeagleCup_Map2 Max Players: 12 Build Time: 2.5 hours Compile Time: 1 minute, 34 seconds Average FPS: 182 de_dust2 Average FPS: 92 After doing a rather industrial based map, it only seemed natural to make one with a more natural feel to it. The size is larger than the first map and has a slightly higher level of detail (mainly from the displacements), but the FPS don't suffer too much. Long range accuracy and use of cover will win this map. DeagleCup_Map3 Max Players: 12 Build Time: 8 hours Compile TIme: 2 minutes, 58 seconds Average FPS: 135 de_dust2 Average FPS: 92 As this was the third map, one that was only meant to be played in case of a draw between the other two maps, meant I could do something a little different. Instead of focusing entirly on a single indoor area, or an entire outdoor area, I decided to include both. This also meant the map had a combination fo close-quarters action and some longer range oppertunities. This map also uses the 3D skybox.

This is a map pack for Gun Game.  There are a total of eight maps in this pack.  Some of them have buy zones, but they can still be played in Gun Game because the Buy Zones get disabled. I hope you enjoy this Gun Game map pack!

Looking at the screen shots from top to bottom:
1. gg_deagle_ultimate - 36 Spawn points, 18 per team
2. gg_lost_temple - 44 Spawns, 22 per team
3. fy_apt_complex - 52 Spawn Points, 26 per team
4. fy_chateau - 44 Spawn points, 22 per team
5. gg_veranda2 & fy_chancellery - 32 spawns & 52 Spawns
6. gg_trenches & gg_fy_courtyard_chaos -  32 spawns & 36 spawns

Install Instructions:  Extract everything in the .rar file to your “cstrike/maps/” folder.
